(101, 'Website development similar towww.agroamerica.com by Jeff Miller', 1, 7, 3, 2, '', 2, 58, 3, 'Client 1:\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThese are the requirements he sent us:\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n1.  Latest version of WordPress .  WordPress CMS allows editing the content on the site myself. Site theme designed around my business colors, logo and images.\r\n\r\n2.  Up to 18 pages of text with images. (ex. About us, Services, Testimonials, etc.) Site Content is provided by me. You will proof read but I know my business best.\r\n\r\n3.  Up to 3 Basic Business Plugins such as Forms, Calendar, Newsletter system, Forum etc.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n4.  Mobile Responsive Layout (Site automatically sizes for mobile browsers)\r\n\r\n5.  Social Media Icons (Facebook, Linkedin, Twitter, etc.)\r\n\r\n6.  â€œContact Usâ€ form that sends submissions by email.\r\n\r\n7.  Custom favicon (small icon on browser tab of my company logo)\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n8.   SEO Optimized including Site Map and Metadata. (No SEO campaign included. Just optimized for SEO) \r\n\r\n9.   Google Analytics so I can see how many people have visited my site.\r\n\r\n10.  Integrated Paralx images and/or embedded video.\r\n\r\n11.  I want a different color pallet. you choose for me but let it be nice.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nHe says he likes this website as an example (heâ€™s in the agro business):\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nhttp://www.agroamerica.com\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nIâ€™m thinking we might need a nice template thatâ€™s similar to the above site. Suggestions?\r\n\r\nWhile the above site is in Spanish, his site will be 100% English.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n', 'Scope of Work \r\n\r\n1. Development of the website in Wordpress - a content management system.\r\n\r\n2. Home-page will have an attractive image slider.\r\n\r\n3. Approx 18 pages designed in user friendly manner in English language.\r\n\r\n4. Enquiry form for visitors at prominent places in the website.\r\n\r\n5. Contact us page will show the address with marking in Google Map.\r\n\r\n6. Multimedia Gallery Page for photos and videos.\r\n\r\n7. Upto 3 basic plugin such as Forms, Newsletter, Forum etc. ( did not get how calendar would make sense. He could perhaps have a blog. Only basic level plugin is included. If a paid plugin is chosen by client, cost is not included) \r\n\r\n8. Custom favicon (Small icon on browser tab of company logo.)\r\n\r\n9. SEO Optimized including Site Map and Metadata. (No SEO campaign included. Just optimized for SEO) \r\n10.  Google Analytics so I can see how many people have visited my site.\r\n11.  Integrated Paralx images and/or embedded video.\r\n\r\n12. A Latest news/update section where latest news/highlights can be displayed.\r\n\r\n13. Social Media Linking - Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn.\r\n\r\n14. Responsive development to display well on mobile browsers.\r\n\r\n15. The website will be compliant with the W3C standards.\r\n16. The website will be compliant across all major internet browsers.\r\n\r\nCost of developing the website if a nice base template is chosen: US$ 1500 + 5% PayPal fee.\r\n\r\n\r\n', '1500', '11-06-2015', '2015-08-01', '1500.00', '', 'Jeff Miller project', '2015-07-03 12:36:15', '2015-07-03 12:42:21', 4, 4),
(102, 'Redevelop questforexcellence.net using Wordpress with an ecommerce shopping cart type plugin. ', 1, 7, 3, 2, '', 2, 58, 3, 'We had to update PHP on our server due to security issues, so this broke a few older websites. One of them was questforexcellence.net. We have approval to â€œremakeâ€ the site using Wordpress with an ecommerce shopping cart type plugin. Currently the client uses Authorize.net and pays about $22 month for this service (plus the discount rate on all sales) whether heâ€™s selling anything or not. For the very small volume he does this seems like overkill â€“ so if you have suggestions for something that could save him $$ that would be appreciated. I know there are many offsite processors out there that work with WordPress that have no monthly fee.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThe idea here is to update the look of Questforexcellence.net (using the same color scheme and artwork) â€“ perhaps a template that is congruent with the â€œlookâ€ thatâ€™s there now would work?\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nYou would not need to add any content. Just set up the site+ecommerce (whether thatâ€™s a shopping cart or an offsite processor) but whatever it is IT MUST BE EASY FOR THE CLIENT TO UPDATE PRODUCTS.\r\n\r\n ', 'Estimate for Client#2 questforexcellence.net\r\n\r\nI would suggest client to use Wordpress WooCommerce Free version - it is a very user-friendly and best wordpress plugin for shopping cart using wordpress. The free version would suffice for all the basic shopping requirements which client currently has.\r\n\r\nFor Payment Gateway, PayPal might suit client as there is no initial/monthly fee. Most of our small business clients use PayPal as gateway. \r\nHere''s the link: https://www.paypal.com/in/webapps/mpp/paypal-fees\r\n\r\nScope of Work\r\n1. Wordpress Setup\r\n2. WooCommerce Shopping Cart Setup for Publication and Seminar section of the website\r\n3. PayPal Payment Gateway Setup\r\n4. Theme Installation\r\n5. Theme Setup\r\n6. PSD Mock-up creation for home page based on the chosen theme.\r\n7. Home Page Creation on the website \r\n8. 1 Content Inner Page creation with dummy (or actual) text\r\n9. Setup and Look and Feel adjustments for pages like product listing, cart, checkout,etc.\r\n\r\nShop details\r\n\r\n1. Users will be able to place their orders on the website. \r\n\r\n2. Users will be able to use check out feature available on the website.\r\n\r\n3. View Cart Page : User can see all products added to Cart\r\n\r\n4. Users will be able to make payment for purchasing items on the website by using integrated payment gateway provided by the client.\r\n\r\n5. Users will be able to receive an email for confirmation after an order is placed on the website.\r\n6. The prices will display in a single currency in the shop.\r\n\r\nAdministrative Panel\r\n\r\n1. User Management\r\n\r\n2. Product Management\r\n\r\n3. Shipping: Options of offering free shipping, or flat rate shipping. \r\n\r\n4. Tax: Configure tax settings with tax classes & local tax rates.\r\n\r\n5. Reporting: Birds-eye view of incoming sales\r\n\r\n\r\nOut of Scope\r\nAll content entry\r\nA good theme which is similar to current site will be purchased\r\n\r\nCost: $ 900 + 5% PayPal transaction fee\r\nTimeline: 2-3 weeks', '900', '10-06-2015', '2015-08-01', '900.00', '', 'Jeff Miller project', '2015-07-03 12:41:50', '2015-07-03 12:41:50', 4, 0),
(103, 'Move SQL database from old site to new one for Jeffreydesign.com)', 1, 7, 3, 2, '', 2, 58, 3, 'I have a website of my own that I am working on. (Jeffreydesign.com) and I have it setup with a template that I like however I would like to move the SQL database from the old site into the new one. Itâ€™s all on the server. Since the old site was using an old version of ZenCart and the new site has the latest version, I assume that the SQL DB is somewhat different but should not be too difficult to transfer. Estimate? There are not that many items. I would only want the items that are live, nothing that was previously deleted or sold.', '\r\nWe have some queries in order to estimate the effort\r\n\r\n1. Do you want the entire SQL DB to move ( it has product categories + products + orders + a lot of other stuff like text content pages, etc ) OR do you want to move only the product categories and products?\r\n\r\n2. How many products are there?\r\n\r\n3. What is the old zen cart version and the new zen cart version?\r\n\r\n4. Is it possible to give access credentials to both the zen-cart installs?', 'Not sent', '10-06-2015', '2015-08-01', '1000.00', '', 'Jeff Miller project, Zencart', '2015-07-03 12:46:06', '2015-07-03 12:46:06', 4, 0),
